  "notes": "Executable parity coverage for metaobject entry reads and definition-scoped child connections. The spec replays no-data reads, then stages the captured definition and entry through public GraphQL mutations in snapshot mode. Seeded entry targets compare `metaobjects`, `metaobject`, and `metaobjectByHandle`; definition child targets compare `metaobjectDefinition(id:).metaobjects` and `metaobjectDefinitionByType(type:).metaobjects` against real Shopify readback while allowing only synthetic ids, cursors, and timestamps to vary. Runtime tests cover aliases, unknown `field(key:)`, empty `referencedBy`, stable local cursors, sorting, reverse pagination, and field-value query filtering beyond the single-entry captured fixture."
